text:
Seafood that has been poached 
alongside tomatoes, olive oil, 
and more.

Adzuki beans, agar cubes, peaches, 
and oranges, arranged together and 
topped with brown-sugar syrup.

Apples dipped in choux batter and 
fried in oil, served with a topping of 
sprinkled sugar.

A sweet beverage made from apples 
that have been simmered with water 
and sugar. Serve either hot or cold.

A pie-like pudding made from apples, 
pan-fried on high heat, baked in a 
crust of buttery bread, then chilled.

A freshly baked pie stuffed with thin 
slices of apple.

Thinly-stretched dough topped with 
tomato sauce, cheese, and basil 
leaves.

Alternating layers of bacon and fish, 
salted and wrapped in well-kneaded 
rye dough, then baked in an oven.

Minced meat, onions, potatoes, and 
more, all wrapped and baked inside 
a pie crust.

A potato, baked whole, then split 
and topped with cheese, beans, and 
other toppings.

Bread made with baking soda in 
place of yeast.

Custard and berry jam baked 
between layers of tart dough.

Berry juice, thickened with potato 
starch and chilled, then served with 
fresh cream on top.

Soft, warm cream with added sugar, 
gelatin, and vanilla, poured in a form 
to set, then topped with berry sauce.

Sausages prepared with animal 
blood in the casing, cooked by 
boiling.

Chunks of beef, sautéed with onions, 
then simmered in grape sauce with 
added butter.

Chilies that have been stewed with 
cheese in water, then stewed again 
with added tomatoes and garlic.

Boiled eggs that have been wrapped 
in ground beef, then breaded and 
deep-fried.

Berries and red syrup, simmered 
and cooled until thick, served with 
a scoop of cold ice cream.

Tomatoes cooked in sweet vinegar 
along with onions, spices, and 
other ingredients.

Dried cod that has been soaked in 
lye for rehydration, then rinsed and 
boiled. Has a soft, jiggly consistency.

A mix of fresh cabbage and assorted 
nuts, topped with dressing just 
before serving.

Pieces of raw fruit, placed on sticks 
and sprinkled with spicy powder.

A scoop of peach sorbet topped with 
chili sauce.

A salad topped with chili sauce made 
from many different spices.

Dough extruded through a star- 
shaped nozzle, fried in oil, then 
coated in sugar, honey, and more.

Stretched dough, covered in butter, 
sprinkled with cinnamon and sugar, 
then rolled up and baked in an oven.

Potatoes, fish, and more placed in a 
two-handed pot with cream, then 
baked in an oven.

Cod and potatoes, boiled in milk, 
then mashed into a paste. Served 
as a spread over bread.

A variety of vegetables, apples, and 
more, all blended together as a soup.

A soup made with stewed sausage, 
beans, and vegetables. The base 
may vary depending on the cook.

A large round loaf of bread made 
from only rye flour, salt, and water.

Crispy croquettes filled with creamy 
white sauce.

Chilled custard with sugar sprinkled 
on top, scorched on the surface to 
create a thin crust of caramel.

Pancakes that were spread thin and 
cooked as crêpes, then covered 
with jam and rolled before serving.

Extremely thin, crunchy, cracker-like 
bread made with simple wheat flour, 
salt, and water.

Bread with butter between several 
layers of dough, folded many times, 
then baked into a crescent moon.

A dough of flour, butter, and sugar 
used to cover a variety of simmered 
fruits, then baked in an oven.

Grilled chicken meat, simmered in 
a curry sauce with tomatoes and 
cream as a base.

A sweet bread in the shape of a 
dome, baked with dried slices of 
various fruits mixed into the dough.

Minced meat, vegetables, and bread 
crumbs, all seasoned with herbs, 
then wrapped in dough and boiled.

A bowl of cooked rice topped with a 
poached egg and soy sauce.

A thick soup made with fish and 
fresh cream.

Dough made with white fish as a 
base, then fried in butter.

Mounds of fried dough, stuffed with 
a variety of jams and creams.

A carefully gutted carp dunked 
whole into hot oil.

Pork belly stir-fried with a variety 
of vegetables that have been pickled 
with spices, including chilies.

Small sardines that have been fried 
whole in a bed of olive oil.

A variety of fresh vegetables, stir- 
fried with garlic.

Fruit coated entirely in syrup or 
sugar, with a stick as a handle. 
Makes a great snack.

Ham, apple slices, and cheese 
arranged atop a slice of freshly 
toasted bread.

An assortment of dried fruits that 
have been wrapped and baked inside 
pie dough.

A wedge of cheese made from 
farm-fresh dairy.

Green peas that have been mashed 
alongside milk or butter.

A crêpe, flambéed with orange juice 
for extra fragrance.

A light and fluffy sponge cake 
covered with jam.

Oven-baked cookies with a dimple 
of jam in the center.

Mutton and cabbage, stewed in the 
same dish until the cabbage softens.

Herring and onions that have been 
pickled in vinegar and sugar.

Salmon marinated with salt, sugar, 
and herbs. Enjoy its unique aroma!

Meaty dango covered in heavy cream 
sauce. The sauce contains a sweet 
jam that complements the meat.

A mixture of fermented beans or 
wheat, stirred into hot water and 
served with tofu or seaweed.

A batter of eggs, flour, and milk that 
has been poured over a griddle and 
delicately fried.

A cake with sliced, caramelized nuts 
mixed into the dough, featuring a 
middle layer of custard cream.

Assorted nuts that have been 
simmered in sugar water.

Lightly fried dough containing a 
central layer of crushed nuts 
and syrup.

Rice simmered in a syrup made of 
crushed nuts and milk.
Milk poured over oats, then heated.

Beaten, cooked, and folded eggs 
filled with a variety of ingredients 
such as tomatoes or cheese.

Plentiful onions, sautéed with bacon, 
nestled into quiche dough and baked 
in an oven.

A modest yet flavorful soup made 
with onions, water, and spices.

Slices of rye bread spread with 
butter and generously topped with 
cheese, smoked salmon, and more.

Sugar-infused oranges, baked in an 
oven, then coated in chocolate after 
cooling.

A fruit preserve made from oranges 
that have been boiled with sugar and 
water while still in their skins.

Rice cooked in a wide, flat pan along 
with a soupy mix of vegetables and 
assorted seafoods.

Peaches baked in buttery dough, 
then sprinkled with powdered sugar 
just before eating.

Juice squeezed from fresh peaches 
then stirred and frozen. To be eaten 
with a spoon.

Onion and tomato pickles wrapped 
in a roll of vinegar-pickled herring.

Simmered sour cream with wheat 
flour and milk. Served with sugar 
and melted butter.

Pork and onions wrapped and baked 
in a dough made from potatoes.

Pan-fried dough made with grated 
potatoes.

A thick, comforting soup made with 
soft, tender potatoes.

Slices of dry-cured ham made from 
high-quality pork.

Ground beef and tofu, stir-fried with 
a variety of spices, including chilies. 
Warning: extremely spicy!

Whole chili peppers that have been 
pickled in vinegar.

Boiled rice, mixed with egg wash, 
cheese, salt, and pepper, then coated 
with breadcrumbs and fried.

Rice that has been pan-fried in 
butter, then cooked in stock with 
added spices.

Pork belly meat, roasted and baked 
in a pan with the skin intact.

Seasoned salmon that has been 
grilled in an oven.

Bread rolls baked in the shape of 
roses. The inside is hollow, while the 
outer crust is crispy and fragrant.

Salted salmon and potatoes, heaped, 
then covered with an egg-and-milk 
mixture and baked in an oven.

Thin, rolled slices of salted pork 
belly rubbed in spices, then baked 
on skewers with various condiments.

A savory sandwich made to look like 
a cake, decorated with filleted fish in 
the shape of a flower.
Thin slices of assorted raw fish.

Chopped pork belly meat, fried and 
served with apples that were pan- 
fried on high heat with very little oil.

A variety of seafoods stewed in olive 
oil with garlic.

Fresh clover that has been arranged 
and sprinkled with olive oil or 
vinegar.

Various meats, marinated in oil and 
spices, then grilled on skewers.

Eel that has been gutted and smoked 
whole. You can even eat the skin!

A thick beverage made by crushing, 
mixing, and swirling a variety of 
fruit pieces together.

A treat of various nuts mixed with 
sugar or meringue, then formed into 
thin bars and chilled to set.

Soft balls of bread dough that have 
been steamed with warmed butter 
and milk inside a lidded pot.

A lamb shank that has been cured in 
salt, then steamed.

Meatballs and beans that have been 
stewed alongside onions and other 
ingredients.

Shredded cabbage mixed with salt 
and spices, then pickled inside a pot 
or jar.

Pan-fried mutton, stewed alongside 
potatoes and onions.

Mashed potatoes that have been 
stewed with herbs and milk.

Salted pork shank that has been 
stewed among vegetables and herbs 
for several hours.

Sheep innards, onions, and herbs 
packed and boiled inside of a 
sheep's stomach.

A hearty soup, loaded with a wide 
variety of vegetables.

Bite-sized pieces of fried pancake, 
slathered in melted butter, and 
topped with powdered sugar.

A fluffy pizza made with thick-baked 
crêpe dough.

Thick-cut potato fries, to be eaten 
with a preferred condiment.

Alternating layers of espresso- 
soaked biscuits and special cream, 
left to chill until set.

Spices simmered in chicken soup. 
It's known for its complex fragrance 
and sour spiciness.

A cake with meringue in its batter, 
baked in rings of different sizes and 
stacked to resemble a conical tree.

Blocks of wheat or cake flour with 
added sugar, steamed to harden.

Thinly sliced raw veal fillet, rolled 
up and topped with cheese, sauce, 
and more.

Various vegetables that have been 
cut into stick-like shapes for easy 
dipping into condiments or sauces.

Sausages made from mutton and 
fresh bacon. Contain additional 
herbs for an extra bit of flavor.
